author: shoulder
glottocode: 3SG form is zero marked; pahi- inflecting root for other person-numbers

author: man/male
glottocode: Can also occur with inalienable possessor affixes when referring to a male child (kin)

author: woman/female
glottocode: Can also occur with inalienable possessor affixes when referring to a female child (kin)

author: dull, blunt
glottocode: also tugil, where <i> possibly represents fossilised 3SG infix

author: dry
glottocode: dekih 'to dry up' e.g., of a well

author: to hide
glottocode: -ɸina is transitive, has to have detransitivising h-

author: at
glottocode: also aka where a- is the 3SG prefix
